The `vote` handler checks that `hot_key` is present in `self.extra_signatories`. The `else` branch rejects any other script purpose, ensuring this validator is only used for governance voting.

```aiken
use aiken/collection/list
use aiken/crypto.{VerificationKeyHash}
use aiken/interval
use cardano/transaction.{Transaction}

validator hot_cold_drep(
  cold_key: VerificationKeyHash,
  hot_key: VerificationKeyHash,
  open_from: Int,
  open_until: Int,
) {
  vote(_redeemer: Void, _voter: Credential, self: Transaction) -> Bool {
    let cold_signed = list.has(self.extra_signatories, cold_key)
    let hot_signed = list.has(self.extra_signatories, hot_key)
    let in_window =
      interval.between(open_from, open_until)
        |> interval.includes(self.validity_range)
    cold_signed || (hot_signed && in_window)
  }

  else(_) {
    fail
  }
}
```

- The cold key is always authorized.
- The hot key is only authorized when the transaction validity range is entirely within `[open_from, open_until]`.
- `interval.includes` checks that `self.validity_range` is contained within the allowed window.

Dentro del handler `vote`, el parámetro `self` es de tipo `Transaction`. Los votos están disponibles en el campo `self.votes`, cuyo tipo es:

```aiken
Pairs<Voter, Pairs<GovernanceActionId, Vote>>
```

Esto significa que es una lista de pares donde cada entrada asocia un `Voter` con sus votos sobre distintas `GovernanceActionId`. Por ejemplo, para verificar que se emitieron votos en la transacción:

```aiken
