    )
  }

  else(_) {
    fail
  }
}
```

Este validador recibe una lista de administradores como redeemer y comprueba que al menos uno de ellos aparece en `self.extra_signatories` usando `list.any` y `list.has`.

Use `list.concat` to merge the two lists, then `list.count` with a predicate to count matching elements:

```aiken
use aiken/collection/list

let left = [5, 15, 20]
let right = [3, 11, 8]

let combined = list.concat(left, right)
// combined == [5, 15, 20, 3, 11, 8]

let above_ten = list.count(combined, fn(n) { n > 10 })
// above_ten == 3  (15, 20, 11)
```

- `list.concat(left, right)` creates a new list with all elements of `left` followed by all elements of `right`.
- `list.count(list, predicate)` returns the number of elements for which the predicate returns `True`.

Neither operation modifies the original lists since Aiken is immutable.

