output:
By extracting the magic numbers into named module constants, the code becomes more readable and the values can be reused across the project. Constants are inlined by the compiler, so there is no runtime cost.

```aiken
use cardano/transaction.{Transaction, OutputReference}
use aiken/collection/list

const min_inputs = 3
const max_inputs = 10

validator token_threshold {
  spend(
    _datum: Option<Void>,
    _redeemer: Void,
    _own_ref: OutputReference,
    self: Transaction,
  ) -> Bool {
    let total_inputs = self.inputs |> list.length
    total_inputs >= min_inputs && total_inputs <= max_inputs
  }
}
```

The constants `min_inputs` and `max_inputs` are fully evaluated at compile-time and can be used anywhere a literal integer could appear — including `when` branches and `if/else` conditions.

Declara la constante a nivel de módulo y úsala directamente dentro del validador:

```aiken
use cardano/assets
use cardano/transaction.{Transaction, Output}
use aiken/collection/list

const min_lovelace: Int = 2_000_000

validator check_min_ada {
  spend(
    _datum: Option<Void>,
    _redeemer: Void,
    _own_ref: transaction.OutputReference,
    self: Transaction,
  ) -> Bool {
    list.any(
      self.outputs,
      fn(output: Output) -> Bool {
        assets.lovelace_of(output.value) >= min_lovelace
      },
    )
  }
}
```

La constante `min_lovelace` es visible en todo el módulo porque está declarada en el nivel superior con `const`.

```aiken
use cardano/transaction.{Transaction, OutputReference}
use aiken/collection/list
use aiken/crypto.{VerificationKeyHash}

validator check_signatory {
  spend(
    _datum: Option<Void>,
    _redeemer: Void,
    _own_ref: OutputReference,
    self: Transaction,
  ) -> Bool {
    let has_signatories: Bool = !list.is_empty(self.extra_signatories)
    has_signatories
  }
}
```

Here `let has_signatories: Bool = ...` uses an explicit type annotation on a local binding. The annotation `Bool` is redundant (the compiler infers it), but it acts as documentation and makes the intent clear.

