In Aiken, section headings are a documentation organizational tool for library modules. They are written as double-slash comments (`//`) whose payload starts with a markdown heading marker (`#`, `##`, `###`, etc.).

They instruct the documentation generation tool to create a new heading in the sidebar and in the main content. The heading size and surrounding margins depend on its importance level (`#` being the most important).

Example:
```aiken
// ## Constructing

/// Construct a new `MyType` holding a value.
fn new(value) -> MyType {}

/// Construct an empty `MyType`.
fn empty() -> MyType {}

// ## Inspecting

/// Obtain the value, if any, at the given key.
fn get(self, key) -> Option<value> {}
```

Note: Section headings use `//` (not `///`), while doc comments for individual functions use `///`.

```aiken
use aiken/collection/list
use aiken/crypto.{VerificationKeyHash}
use cardano/assets.{PolicyId}
use cardano/transaction.{Transaction}

